==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neo-Darwinism
<hw>Ne`o-Dar"win*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The theory
which holds natural selection, as explained by Darwin, to be the chief
factor in the evolution of plants and animals, and denies the
inheritance of acquired characters; -- esp. opposed to
<contr>Neo-Lamarckism</contr>. Weismannism is an example of extreme
Neo-Darwinism.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ne`o-Dar*win"i*an</wf>,
<pos>a.</pos> & <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neodymium</ent>⟦br⟧
